In this press briefing, Press Secretary Jay Carney discusses various topics. He starts by mentioning the positive employment report that shows private sector payrolls increasing by 268,000 in April. He also highlights the President's visit to Allison Transmission, a leader in hybrid technology, to emphasize the administration's commitment to diversifying energy requirements and reducing dependence on imported oil. Additionally, Carney mentions the President's upcoming visit to Fort Campbell to meet with members of the 101st Airborne Division and acknowledges their remarkable history and service. Carney then responds to questions about the President's speech to troops, the threat of retaliation from al Qaeda, and the possibility of a Medicare plan from Republican congressional leaders. He also addresses concerns about gas prices, the President's commitment to comprehensive immigration reform, and the upcoming events on the President's schedule.